<p>I wish to animate a div to make it appear and slide down with jQuery.</p>  <p>I have got my script to work where you hover over an image and another div slides in, should the user leave the mouse hover, the div will slide up and disappear.</p>  <p><strong>Problem:</strong></p>  <p>The first time i hover over the image, nothing happens. I have to leave my mouse and hover over it a second time for the effect to start working, I dont get why this is???</p>  <p><strong>jQuery:</strong></p>  <pre><code>function show_action(){     $(function(){         $(".action").hide();         $(".logo").hover(             function(){ $(".action").slideDown(); },             function(){ $(".action").slideUp(); }         );     }); } </code></pre>  <p><strong>CSS:</strong></p>  <pre><code>#action_text{     display:none; } </code></pre>  <p><strong>HTML:</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="center_container"&gt;   &lt;div class="action" id="action_text"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Click To Upload&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;img src="images/logo.png" class="logo" onmouseover="show_action();"&gt;  &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>